l. The proposed model outperforms binary classification\nmodels on the clinical X-VIRAL dataset that contains 5,977 viral pneumonia (no\nCOVID-19) cases, 18,619 non-viral pneumonia cases, and 18,774 healthy controls.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 27 Mar 2020 11:32:18 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 28 Jun 2020 04:16:00 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sun, 27 Sep 2020 01:29:10 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 2 Dec 2020 00:05:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-12-03"}
